                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2151/46.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gummeré</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>States that it is currently reported that the uncle of the Sultan has been
                    proclaimed Sultan at Morocco City. Says that he has been informed by the Spanish
                    minister that the Spanish consul at Mogador has telegraphed him to the same
                    effect. Adds that it is reported that all Christians have left Fez for the
                    coast, and that all is quiet at Tangier.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
